==English==
===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈstɒkfɪʃ/}}

===Etymology 1===
From Middle Low German / Middle Dutch ''[[stokvisch]]'', of unknown origin.

====Noun====
{{en-noun|es|pl2=stockfish}}

# A [[cod]] (or similar fish) having been cut open and [[cured]] in the open air without salt.
#:*'''1819''': So the Prior of Saint Botolph’s hobbled back again into the refectory, to preside over the '''stockfish''' and ale, which was just serving out for the friars’ breakfast. — Walter Scott, ''Ivanhoe''

===Etymology 2===
From Afrikaans, from Dutch ''[[stokvis]]''.

====Noun====
{{en-noun|es|pl2=stockfish}}

# (''South Africa'') The [[South African hake]], ''Merluccius capensis''.